It remains to be seen whether Reus will continue the trend by emulating another emoji symbol, but despite it being all smiles in Europe, his side are struggling in the Bundesliga.

They have qualified from their Champions League group with ease and should top the standings after Arsenal squandered a three-goal lead against Anderlecht.

But domestically Jurgen Klopp's side are joint bottom with just two wins in 10 games.

They face third-place Borussia Monchengladbach on Sunday at the Westfalenstadion.

